separable ODE in 1 dimension 
$ 
  (#d x)/(#d t) = f(t) g(x) 
  &--> 1/g(x) #d x = f(t) #d t \
  &--> x = G^(-1)(F(t)) 
$ 
where $G = integral 1/g(x) #d x, F = integral f(t) #d t$, initial value undetermined

*Example*
- $f(t) = a, g(x) = x$. $x(t) = x(0) exp(a t)$
- $f(t) = 1, g(x) = x^2$. $x(t) = 1/(1/x(0) - t)$

